1
00:00:00,438 --> 00:00:03,091
<i>The Library!
So big it doesn't need a name.</i>

2
00:00:03,191 --> 00:00:05,480
Someone's got in.
Someone's in my library.

3
00:00:05,580 --> 00:00:07,295
4,022 saved.

4
00:00:07,495 --> 00:00:08,515
No survivors.

5
00:00:08,615 --> 00:00:11,141
- Others are coming.
- What... others?

6
00:00:16,883 --> 00:00:19,537
Professor River Song, archaeologist.

7
00:00:19,637 --> 00:00:21,168
You've seen me before, then?

8
00:00:21,331 --> 00:00:25,643
The real world is a lie,
and your nightmares are real.

9
00:00:26,785 --> 00:00:28,962
- What's CAL?!
- The Library is real.

10
00:00:29,244 --> 00:00:33,187
There are people trapped in there,
people who need to be saved.

11
00:00:33,556 --> 00:00:35,527
There's a neural relay
in the communicator.

12
00:00:35,627 --> 00:00:37,390
<i>Sometimes it can hold an impression</i>

13
00:00:37,490 --> 00:00:40,068
<i>of a living consciousness
for a short time after death.</i>

14
00:00:40,168 --> 00:00:43,562
The shadows are moving again.
Only you can save them.

15
00:00:43,662 --> 00:00:46,220
The piranhas of the air,
the Vashta Nerada.

16
00:00:49,210 --> 00:00:50,950
Donna Noble has been saved.

17
00:00:51,448 --> 00:00:53,331
Donna Noble has been saved.

18
00:00:53,431 --> 00:00:56,470
<i>- Who turned out the lights?
- Donna Noble has left the Library.</i>

19
00:00:56,941 --> 00:00:59,199
<i>Donna Noble has been saved.
Who turned out the lights?</i>

20
00:00:59,299 --> 00:01:03,150
Donna Noble has left the Library.
Donna Noble has been saved.

21
00:01:03,250 --> 00:01:06,550
<i>- Who turned out the lights?
- Donna Noble has left the Library.</i>

22
